definitions.definition: To value , do, or choose something first, or before other things.
examples: When I don't have time to buy everything at the store, I prioritize fresh fruit and vegetables over foods like rice or noodles.

definitions.definition: To arrange or list a group of things in order of priority or importance .
To rank something as having high priority.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To value , do, or choose something first, or before other things.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , intransitive ) To arrange or list a group of things in order of priority or importance .
( transitive ) To rank something as having high priority.
